<figureCitation box="[151,248,402,429]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStart-2="FIGURE 3" captionStart-3="FIGURE 4" captionStart-4="FIGURE 5" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1314,1338]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1824,1848]" captionStartId-2="4.[151,250,1347,1371]" captionStartId-3="5.[151,250,697,721]" captionStartId-4="5.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,776,1290]" captionTargetBox-1="[269,1317,181,1800]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1436,181,1323]" captionTargetBox-3="[155,1429,187,670]" captionTargetBox-4="[151,1427,818,1920]" captionTargetId-0="figure-208@2.[151,1436,776,1290]" captionTargetId-1="figure-20@3.[269,1317,181,1800]" captionTargetId-2="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1323]" captionTargetId-3="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,673]" captionTargetId-4="figure-75@5.[151,1436,818,1920]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionTargetPageId-2="4" captionTargetPageId-3="5" captionTargetPageId-4="5" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp. from Valle del Lunarejo, Rivera, Uruguay. A. Live male. B. Two specimens found under cow dung, one of them inside a nest." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Somatic characters of Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp. A. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), anterior body rings, dorsal view. B. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), middle body rings, dorsal view. C. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), posterior body rings, dorsal view. D. Non type ♂ (FCE-Myr 0556), left antenna. E. Non type ♂ (FCE-Myr 0556), ventral gnathochilarium. F. Non type ♂ (FCE-Myr 0556), dorsal gnathochilarium. G. Non type ♂ (FCE-Myr 0767), sternite 4 with a single pair of fused projections. H. Non type ♂ (FCE-Myr 0767), posterior sternites without modifications. Abbreviations: L: lingual lobes; M: mentum; O: ozopore; P: projection; S: stipes. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (A–D, G–H), 0.5 mm (E–F)." captionText-2="FIGURE 3. Sexual characters of Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp. A. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, mesal view. B. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, lateral view. C. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, ventral view. D. Paratype ♀ (FCE-Myr 0664), left vulva, ventral view. Abbreviations: Ap: acropodital process; Ca: cannula; Cx: coxa; Ev: external valve; Iv: internal valve; Op: operculum; Pf: prefemur; PfP: prefemoral process; Pg: prostatic groove; S: solenomere; SpP: spiniform process. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A–C), 0.2 mm (D). Photographed by: Damián Hagopián." captionText-3="FIGURE 4. Gonopod drawings of Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp., holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod. A. Mesal view. B. Lateral view. C. Ventral view. Abbreviations: Ap: acropodital process; Ca: cannula; Cx: coxa; Pf: prefemur; PfP: prefemoral process; Pg: prostatic groove; S: solenomere; SpP: spiniform process. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." captionText-4="FIGURE 5. Distribution map of Sandalodesmus species." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621305" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621307" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621311" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621313" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621315" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6621305/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6621307/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6621311/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6621313/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/6621315/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Figs 1–5</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
