<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="262" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,474,753]" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,474,500]" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males differ from all other species of the genus by the following combination of characters: prefemoral process (PfP) small, Z-shaped, twisted internally and directed parallel to acropodital branch (
<figureCitation box="[1180,1272,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1347,1371]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1323]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1323]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sexual characters of Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp. A. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, mesal view. B. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, lateral view. C. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, ventral view. D. Paratype ♀ (FCE-Myr 0664), left vulva, ventral view. Abbreviations: Ap: acropodital process; Ca: cannula; Cx: coxa; Ev: external valve; Iv: internal valve; Op: operculum; Pf: prefemur; PfP: prefemoral process; Pg: prostatic groove; S: solenomere; SpP: spiniform process. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A–C), 0.2 mm (D). Photographed by: Damián Hagopián." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6621311/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1283,1321,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,697,721]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,187,670]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,673]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Gonopod drawings of Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp., holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod. A. Mesal view. B. Lateral view. C. Ventral view. Abbreviations: Ap: acropodital process; Ca: cannula; Cx: coxa; Pf: prefemur; PfP: prefemoral process; Pg: prostatic groove; S: solenomere; SpP: spiniform process. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6621313/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">4A</figureCitation>
), prostatic groove (Pg) sinuous and S-shaped along the acropodite, ending upon an elongated prostatic apex (
<figureCitation box="[1277,1372,546,572]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1347,1371]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1323]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1323]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sexual characters of Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp. A. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, mesal view. B. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, lateral view. C. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, ventral view. D. Paratype ♀ (FCE-Myr 0664), left vulva, ventral view. Abbreviations: Ap: acropodital process; Ca: cannula; Cx: coxa; Ev: external valve; Iv: internal valve; Op: operculum; Pf: prefemur; PfP: prefemoral process; Pg: prostatic groove; S: solenomere; SpP: spiniform process. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A–C), 0.2 mm (D). Photographed by: Damián Hagopián." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6621311/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1386,1424,546,572]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,697,721]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,187,670]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,673]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Gonopod drawings of Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp., holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod. A. Mesal view. B. Lateral view. C. Ventral view. Abbreviations: Ap: acropodital process; Ca: cannula; Cx: coxa; Pf: prefemur; PfP: prefemoral process; Pg: prostatic groove; S: solenomere; SpP: spiniform process. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6621313/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">4A</figureCitation>
), acropodite process (Ap) broad and round, elongated, hood-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[928,1057,582,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1347,1371]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1323]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1323]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sexual characters of Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp. A. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, mesal view. B. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, lateral view. C. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, ventral view. D. Paratype ♀ (FCE-Myr 0664), left vulva, ventral view. Abbreviations: Ap: acropodital process; Ca: cannula; Cx: coxa; Ev: external valve; Iv: internal valve; Op: operculum; Pf: prefemur; PfP: prefemoral process; Pg: prostatic groove; S: solenomere; SpP: spiniform process. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A–C), 0.2 mm (D). Photographed by: Damián Hagopián." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6621311/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Figs 3A–C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1072,1142,582,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,697,721]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,187,670]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,673]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Gonopod drawings of Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp., holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod. A. Mesal view. B. Lateral view. C. Ventral view. Abbreviations: Ap: acropodital process; Ca: cannula; Cx: coxa; Pf: prefemur; PfP: prefemoral process; Pg: prostatic groove; S: solenomere; SpP: spiniform process. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6621313/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">4A–C</figureCitation>
), solenomere (S) apically curved, sickle-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[409,502,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1347,1371]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1323]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1323]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sexual characters of Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp. A. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, mesal view. B. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, lateral view. C. Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, ventral view. D. Paratype ♀ (FCE-Myr 0664), left vulva, ventral view. Abbreviations: Ap: acropodital process; Ca: cannula; Cx: coxa; Ev: external valve; Iv: internal valve; Op: operculum; Pf: prefemur; PfP: prefemoral process; Pg: prostatic groove; S: solenomere; SpP: spiniform process. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A–C), 0.2 mm (D). Photographed by: Damián Hagopián." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6621311/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[514,552,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,697,721]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,187,670]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,673]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Gonopod drawings of Sandalodesmus joachimadisi n. sp., holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod. A. Mesal view. B. Lateral view. C. Ventral view. Abbreviations: Ap: acropodital process; Ca: cannula; Cx: coxa; Pf: prefemur; PfP: prefemoral process; Pg: prostatic groove; S: solenomere; SpP: spiniform process. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6621313/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,474,753]" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,276,654,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Name.</emphasis>
The specific name is a patronymic in honor of the German ecologist and entomologist Joachim Ulrich Adis (1950–2007). He visited the Collection of Myriapoda of Facultad de Ciencias, Universidad de la República, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,289,726,752]" country="Uruguay" name="Montevideo" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Montevideo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[301,399,727,753]" name="Uruguay" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
in 2005 and suggested the need for the study of the underexplored Uruguayan 
<taxonomicName box="[1283,1405,726,752]" class="Diplopoda" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="class">Diplopoda</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
